OL,6,FThe four-day trial resulted in Taylor
OL,7,Fbeing convicted of all offences. He
OL,8,Fwas sentenced on 5 July, and was
OL,9,Fjailed for eight years.
OL,11,FIn a victim impact statement read out
OL,12,Fin court, the woman described the
OL,13,Feffect the attack has had on her life.
OL,15,F"My life has changed from that day,"
OL,16,Fshe said. "I permanently feel guilty
OL,17,Fand dirty ` I feel like I can't get
OL,18,Fclean.
